  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    The User Story-Driven Development practice describes how to capture requirements with user stories and how the user&#xD;
    stories&amp;nbsp;influence or guide later decisions in the development lifecycle. User stories are an important input to&#xD;
    other practices.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    User stories are prioritized, estimated, decomposed into tasks, and scheduled&amp;nbsp;as part of project management&#xD;
    practices.&amp;nbsp; User story details guide the design, implementation, and testing&amp;nbsp;of the story.&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
